cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR

This paper deals with training a text classification model and optimizing on bias minimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses measuring performance independently for different demographic subgroups, which falls under the category of fairness and bias in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with the issue of personal identities, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, the paper discusses measuring bias, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with toxicity classification, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
